&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
Research Questions
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adaptive capacities and interactions.&lt;/strong&gt; How do individual- and community-level capacities, and their interactions, shape not only the adoption but the sustained adoption of climate-smart technologies and practices?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feedbacks and dynamics.&lt;/strong&gt; How do feedbacks between social, behavioral, and environmental dynamics influence long-term livelihood outcomes, including resilience and inequality?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scale.&lt;/strong&gt; How do adaptation decisions at the household level scale across production systems, from subsistence-oriented to more commercial farming, and what do these dynamics reveal about structural inequalities and sustainability?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inequality and resilience.&lt;/strong&gt; How do differentiated adoption trajectories between dominant and marginalized groups shape patterns of livelihood inequality and system-level resilience over time?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
